'''Ji Xinpeng''' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: 吉新鹏, born [[December 30]], [[1977]] in [[Xiamen]], [[Fujian]]) is a [[China|Chinese]] [[badminton]] player.

==Career==
{{MedalTop}}
{{MedalSport | Men's [[Badminton at the Summer Olympics|Badminton]]}}
{{MedalGold  | [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Badminton at the 2000 Summer Olympics|Singles]]}}
{{MedalBottom}}
Ji Xinpeng is the first Chinese badminton player to win the gold medal in the men's singles competition at the [[badminton at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Summer Olympics]], defeating [[Hendrawan]] in the final. Ji's gold medal feat came as a big surprise because no one had expected him to do so since he has never won any tournaments previously. He also defeated Taufik Hidayat and Peter Gade Christensen along the way to the final.

